main event: A white saucer-shaped object was observed moving at very high altitude and very fast speed without any trail or exhaust. It circled to the west, crossed its path, then headed east and disappeared. The observation lasted approximately 1 minute.
interesting points: The sighting took place at Tinker AFB, Oklahoma, and was observed by a civilian witness.
The object was seen using naked eye from the ground, 28 miles northwest of Tinker AFB.
No photographs are present in the report, and the object appeared white in color performing normal maneuvers.
The object was observed moving from south to west before heading east at a very high altitude.
The only known air traffic in the area at the time was an Air Force jet flying locally, which landed at Tinker AFB shortly after the sighting.
